-- Cielo Quarterly Profit Beats Estimates After Market Share Gain
-- B y   F r a n c i s c o   M a r c e l i n o
-- 2012-02-09T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/cielo-quarterly-profit-beats-estimates-after-market-share-gain.html
Cielo SA (CIEL3) ,  Brazil ’s biggest card-
payment processor by market value, posted a 14 percent increase
in fourth-quarter profit that beat analysts’ estimates as the
company increased market share.  Net income was 504.5 million reais ($293 million), up from
443.3 million reais a year earlier, the Barueri-based company
said in a regulatory filing yesterday. That beat the  average 
estimate of 487 million reais in a Bloomberg survey of 14
analysts.  Cielo, led by Chief Executive Officer Romulo de Mello Dias,
said it boosted the firm’s market share to 58 percent at the end
of December, from 57 percent in September and 56 percent in
December 2010.  “The company may benefit from adopting a more aggressive
stance and deliver a higher growth rate in the fourth quarter of
2011 than the third quarter of 2011,” Gustavo Schroden and
Mateus Renault, analysts at Espirito Santos Investment Bank in
 Sao Paulo , wrote in Jan. 18 report to clients. They have a
“buy” rating on the stock,  Total credit-card, debit-card and consumer transactions in
the fourth quarter climbed 26 percent to 95.1 billion from a
year earlier, the company said.  Cielo fell 0.5 percent to 55.96 reais in Sao Paulo trading
yesterday, compared with a gain of 2.8 percent for smaller rival
 Redecard SA (RDCD3)  and a drop of 0.1 percent for the benchmark Bovespa.  To contact the reporter on this story:
